description:
Residence
Located on the Corner of East 67th and Madison, and just moments away from Central Park, this elegant studio is among the most prestigious in Manhattan. The main living space is bright and airy with large industrial grade windows letting in endless natural light that perfectly compliments white oak-wood floors. The space is large and square, which allows for any arrangement of furniture. Off the living space is clean, modern bathroom that was recently renovated with high-end finishes.

The renovated kitchen is brand new, and conveniently separate from the the living and sleeping quarters, and features Bertazzoni professional cooktop and oven, Bosch appliances, and finished with white Caesarstone countertops and backsplash, white lacquer cabinetry, and contemporary black and gold finishes.

Building
25 East 67th Street is located on the corner of Madison Avenue and East 67th Street, a block from Central Park and steps from high-end shopping and world-class restaurants.

Built-in 1928, this sixteen story updated prewar residential building features a full-time doorman, and consists of homes that underwent renovations as of Fall 2019. Each apartment have kitchens updated with Caesarstone countertops and backsplashes, a Bertazzoni professional cooktop and oven as well as a Bosch microwave and refrigerator. Apartments are also outfitted with newly designed bathrooms, Restoration Hardware light fixtures, and select apartments have washer/dryer in unit. Ownership will consider furnished rentals / short term rentals for certain units.

Neighborhood
Twenty Five East Sixty Seven is situated one block from Central park and directly in the glamor and excitement of the famed Lenox Hill neighborhood on the Upper East Side of Manhattan. Known for its designer stores along Madison Avenue, top-rated restaurants, and elegant residential buildings, Lenox Hill is also home to an impressive array of cultural sites including The Frick Collection for art-enthusiasts, and the Park Ave Armory, which hosts tremendous avant-garde exhibitions and performances.

In addition to Open Houses, we are available to tour 7 days a week. Look forward to hearing from you, and please feel free to contact the lead listing agent by phone

The Building: 

Welcome to Tower 77, where contemporary luxury meets the vibrant energy of Brooklyn's Greenpoint neighborhood. Nestled within the heart of one of Brooklyn's most sought-after locales, this iconic tower offers an unparalleled living experience.

Boasting stunning architectural design and panoramic views of the Manhattan skyline and East River, Tower 77 stands as a beacon of modernity in the historic landscape of Greenpoint. • We also boast one of the best, state of the art sauna and pool areas with spectacular terrace access to breathtaking water and city views.

The Neighborhood:

Conveniently located just moments away from the vibrant dining, shopping, and entertainment options of Greenpoint, Tower 77 provides residents with easy access to everything this dynamic neighborhood has to offer. description:
Bright & Spacious 2 Bedroom + Private Balcony with Modern Finishes and Unbeatable Brooklyn Location

This versatile 2 bedroom home offers the ideal layout for roommates, families, or a home office setup—delivering both functionality and modern style. This unit features:
- State-of-the-art kitchen with sleek countertops and stainless steel appliances (including a dishwasher).
- Oversized windows with plenty of natural light
- Ample closet space
- Marble bathroom
- Hardwood floors

This updated building features keyless entry with a virtual doorman, enhanced security, and a brand-new industrial laundry room. Residents can enjoy lively common areas with art, greenery, free WiFi, and entertainment spaces.
Live at the crossroads of Greenpoint and Williamsburg, just minutes from local favorites like McGolrick Park, McCarren Park, and the newly transformed Under the K Bridge Park. With the L and G trains, plus B24 and B48 buses nearby, commuting is easy—but you may never want to leave. Local bars, restaurants, coffee shops, and boutiques create a vibrant community feel right outside your door.

The Building:

Welcome to Tower 77, where contemporary luxury meets the vibrant energy of Brooklyn's Greenpoint neighborhood. Nestled within the heart of one of Brooklyn's most sought-after locales, this iconic tower offers an unparalleled living experience.

Boasting stunning architectural design and panoramic views of the Manhattan skyline and East River, Tower 77 stands as a beacon of modernity in the historic landscape of Greenpoint. Beyond the apartments, Tower 77 offers an array of amenities designed to enhance your daily life.

• We also boast one of the best, state of the art sauna and pool areas with spectacular terrace access to breathtaking water and city views.

Conveniently located just moments away from the vibrant dining, shopping, and entertainment options of Greenpoint, Tower 77 provides residents with easy access to everything this dynamic neighborhood has to offer. With nearby transportation options including the G train and East River Ferry, Manhattan is just a short commute away.

description:
*Spectacular Two Bed Two Bath with and Enormous Lofted Living Space, Large Primary En-Suite, and High-End Finishes Complimented by Endless Natural Light*
Rent Stabilized & In-Unit Laundry 

1A is an absolutely stunning floor-through residence. White-oak floors carry through the home, and reflect an abundance of natural light pouring through the trees of Convent Avenue.

The entry opens to an astoundingly large living/dining room accented with exposed brick. The enormous space comes complete with a fully renovated chef's kitchen boasting stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher, white-quartz countertops and white-lacquer cabinetry.

The hallway off the kitchen is lined with large closets with frosted glass doors, and leads to a luxurious full-guest-bathroom. The queen-sized guest bedroom is large, and comes with additional closet space and has great exposure.

The primary bedroom comes with a double-sink en-suite bathroom featuring both a standing shower and large soaking tub. The room itself is large, and features more large closets with frosted glass doors.

*Location*
Arguably the most picturesque block in all of Manhattan, Convent Avenue is an asthetic display of large weeping trees and stunning preserved architecture. The sidewalks are lined with impressive trees with branches draping branches creating textured shadows in the streets. Either side of the street is composed of gorgeous brownstones and historic churches, both active and converted. Just beyond the serene avenue, the streets open to live NYC action filled with restaurants, cafe’s, shopping, parks and the stunning grounds of City College. As for transportation, subway entrances and bus stops are only moments away.

description:
*Exquisite 1-Bedroom 1-Bath in the Upper East Side*

*The Residence*

Situated within the illustrious Upper East Side, this 1-bedroom residence epitomizes a harmonious blend of grace, convenience, and modern flair. Delve into an environment where every facet has been meticulously curated for opulence.

The generously proportioned Primary Bedroom accommodates a king-sized bed, ensuring a sumptuous sanctuary at day’s end. Sunlight graces the interiors, bestowing a warm, serene milieu.

The expansive living space provides a breathable ambience, tailor-made for leisure and sociability. Ample windows illuminate the area, enhancing the day-to-day vibrancy.

Bathed in sunlight, a commodious alcove stands ready to host a dining set-up.

*The Locale*

Residing in the heart of the Upper East Side places a plethora of gourmet dining options, chic bars, and cultural landmarks at one’s fingertips. Daily essentials are easily met with Whole Foods and Fairway within proximity.
Effortless city navigation is made possible with the nearby Q train and other transit options.
Bask in the Upper East Side’s refined allure, all while relishing in a home that boasts a private balcony, sunlit spaces, and a multifunctional home office zone. This isn’t merely a residence, but a lifestyle intertwining contemporary amenities with the UES’s storied past. Seize the chance to claim this unmatched gem as your own


We accommodate tours seven days a week. For scheduling and inquiries, please connect with the listing agent mentioned at the top of this page. We eagerly look forward to helping you find your new home.

description:
*Welcome to this Spacious Three-Bedroom residence in vibrant Hamilton Heights! This cozy unit offers beautiful hardwood flooring throughout.*

With ample natural light, the spacious and well designed living space welcomes you as you enter, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.

The separate kitchen area features modern appliances, stylish countertops, and plenty of storage, perfect for creating your favorite dishes.

This residence provides versatility and space, allowing you to separate your entertainment and private space.

Located in Hamilton Heights, you’ll have easy access to the neighborhood’s renowned dining, shopping, and cultural attractions.
With excellent public transportation options nearby, you can explore all that New York City has to offer with ease.

This residence is a fantastic option for those seeking a convenient and comfortable urban living experience. Don’t miss your chance to make it your new home!

*Please reach out to lead listing agent for viewings.*

description:
Large, Contemporary One Bedroom Located in an Elevator Building in Hudson Heights

Residence

Welcome to this contemporary, nearly floor-through one-bedroom, beautifully illuminated with natural light and situated in an elevator building west of Broadway. This residence features an expansive layout with high ceilings and gorgeous hardwood floors, creating an elegant and sophisticated atmosphere. The bright and spacious bedroom is secluded from the rest of the apartment and offers ample closet space, pleasant street views, and is designed to accommodate a bed plus additional furniture comfortably.

Building & Location

With a long gated entry and an impressively renovated lobby, This building is located on West 181st and Fort Washington – arguably the best location in Washington Heights. With multiple transportation options just moments away including the A, C, and 1 trains, you are never far from the vibrant food scene of the neighborhood. The serene and well-maintained Bennett Park is only a few blocks away, perfect for a morning jog or a leisurely evening stroll. For coffee lovers, there is a Starbucks just half a block away from the building. You can enjoy your brew as you walk through the picturesque Fort Tryon Park. The building’s proximity to the George Washington Bridge is an added advantage for those who enjoy driving out of the city.

In addition to open houses, we are available seven days a week to provide individual appointments. Reach out to us via text, call, or email today to schedule a viewing. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new home.
